I wanted to hold her close to me,
weep tears on her shoulder,

705
00:49:34,640 --> 00:49:36,517
and engage in oral sex.

706
00:49:36,640 --> 00:49:38,995
It was then that I made
the decision to live,

707
00:49:39,120 --> 00:49:41,156
to live and become a great poet.

708
00:49:41,720 --> 00:49:44,188
I should have been

709
00:49:44,320 --> 00:49:49,110
a pair of ragged claws

710
00:49:49,240 --> 00:49:55,190
scuttling across the floors

711
00:49:55,560 --> 00:49:58,711
of silent seas.

712
00:50:00,480 --> 00:50:02,710
Too sentimental.

713
00:50:04,280 --> 00:50:07,158
That winter
Sonja and I had a wonderful time.

714
00:50:07,280 --> 00:50:10,352
We found a new friend,
Berdykov, the village idiot.

715
00:50:10,480 --> 00:50:14,553
Berdykov would sit smiling for days
and stroke a little piece of velvet.

716
00:50:14,680 --> 00:50:17,319
Sonja would make him happy
by feeding him cookies.

717
00:50:17,440 --> 00:50:20,910
We looked forward to the spring,
when we could have a child of our own.

718
00:50:21,040 --> 00:50:22,553
Little did we know...

719
00:50:23,040 --> 00:50:27,670
War! Napoleon
has invaded Russia! It's war!

720
00:50:31,640 --> 00:50:34,950
Oh, what about all our plans?
We were gonna be parents this year!

721
00:50:35,080 --> 00:50:38,595
There's gonna be a slight change.
Instead, we're gonna be refugees.

722
00:50:38,720 --> 00:50:42,395
- That's terrible!
- We have to take everything and flee.

723
00:50:42,520 --> 00:50:46,513
I'm very good at that. I was the men's
freestyle fleeing champion for two years.

724
00:50:46,640 --> 00:50:50,918
We have to burn the food so the French
don't get it. But it's tough to light borscht.

725
00:50:51,040 --> 00:50:53,270
- Boris, I have an idea.
- What?

726
00:50:54,400 --> 00:50:56,550
Let's assassinate Napoleon.

727
00:50:57,120 --> 00:51:00,112
Yeah. Interesting.
Do you want to start knitting dinner?

728
00:51:00,240 --> 00:51:02,549
- I'm serious.
- What do you mean?

729
00:51:02,680 --> 00:51:05,069
I mean, let's you and I kill Napoleon.

730
00:51:05,200 --> 00:51:08,317
You been drinking from
the glass we use for the village idiot?

731
00:51:08,440 --> 00:51:11,955
- It's the answer to our problems.
- It's not the answer. It's an answer.

732
00:51:12,080 --> 00:51:16,517
And it's the wrong answer.
The correct answer is flee. F-L-E-A. Flee.

733
00:51:16,640 --> 00:51:20,076
- The French occupy Moscow. He's there.
- Sonja!

734
00:51:20,200 --> 00:51:23,590
Two innocent-looking types like us
could get in and shoot him.

735
00:51:23,720 --> 00:51:26,154
We'd never get near him,
and if we did, we'd miss.

736
00:51:26,280 --> 00:51:28,236
He's a tough target. He's very small.

737
00:51:28,360 --> 00:51:30,999
Boris, it's our chance
to perform a truly heroic act.

738
00:51:31,120 --> 00:51:33,315
Since when is murder a heroic act?

739
00:51:33,440 --> 00:51:36,830
Violence is justified
in the service of mankind.

740
00:51:36,960 --> 00:51:39,269
- Who said that?
- Attila the Hun.

741
00:51:39,600 --> 00:51:41,511
You're quoting a Hun to me?

742
00:51:41,640 --> 00:51:43,790
Don't you know
that murder carries with it

743
00:51:43,920 --> 00:51:48,550
a moral imperative that transcends
any notion of inherent universal free will?

744
00:51:50,240 --> 00:51:53,038
That is incredibly jejune.

745
00:51:54,440 --> 00:51:56,510
- That's jejune?
- Jejune!

746
00:51:56,640 --> 00:52:00,679
You have the temerity to say that
I'm talking to you out of jejunosity?

747
00:52:00,800 --> 00:52:03,837
I am one of the most june people
in all of the Russias.

748
00:52:03,960 --> 00:52:05,712
I have lvan's old pistol.

749
00:52:05,840 --> 00:52:08,593
Sonja!
Political assassination doesn't work.

750
00:52:08,720 --> 00:52:12,474
Violence leads to violence. He who
lives by the sword dies by the sword.

751
00:52:12,600 --> 00:52:14,477
Well, I'm out of clichés now.

752
00:52:14,600 --> 00:52:18,639
- Are you suggesting passive resistance?
- No, I'm suggesting active fleeing.

753
00:52:18,760 --> 00:52:22,230
- You can't run away all your life.
- I know, but murder.

754
00:52:22,360 --> 00:52:24,316
The most foul of all crimes.

755
00:52:24,440 --> 00:52:28,399
And not abstract murder like shooting
an unknown enemy on the battlefield,

756
00:52:28,520 --> 00:52:31,512
but standing in a closed room
with a live human being

757
00:52:31,640 --> 00:52:33,915
and pulling the trigger, face to face.

758
00:52:34,040 --> 00:52:37,999
And a famous human being, a successful
one, one who earns more than I do.

759
00:52:38,120 --> 00:52:42,398
My God, you figure Napoleon has gotta
be good for 10,000 francs a week.

760
00:52:42,520 --> 00:52:46,479
That's minimum. That's without tips
or extras. Nothing like that.

761
00:52:46,600 --> 00:52:49,592
And me, what am I? He's a great man.

762
00:52:49,720 --> 00:52:53,508
He thinks like the superman
and I'm just a worm,

763
00:52:53,640 --> 00:52:59,317
an insect, some kind of crawling,
disgusting, creeping little vermin.

764
00:53:00,240 --> 00:53:03,835
- You know, you can stop me.
- I will when I disagree.

765
00:53:03,960 --> 00:53:06,076
Sonja. Who are we to kill somebody?

766
00:53:06,200 --> 00:53:09,988
Boris, for the first time in my life
I feel free. Weightless.

767
00:53:10,120 --> 00:53:13,590
I have an exhilarating feeling
of human freedom.

768
00:53:13,720 --> 00:53:15,472
It's called the guillotine.

769
00:53:15,600 --> 00:53:17,033
Oh, look, Boris.

770
00:53:17,160 --> 00:53:20,630
The soft golden dusk is
already transmogrifying itself

771
00:53:20,760 --> 00:53:23,149
into the blue star-sprinkled night.

772
00:53:24,600 --> 00:53:27,114
Careful, cos that gun may be loaded.

773
00:53:27,240 --> 00:53:29,834
Several days later
we set out for Moscow.

774
00:53:29,960 --> 00:53:33,316
We took Berdykov with us partway.
He was on his way to Minsk.

775
00:53:33,440 --> 00:53:37,638
There was a village idiots' convention in
Minsk. Berdykov was planning to attend.

776
00:53:37,760 --> 00:53:40,991
Village idiots from all over Russia
were meeting there.

777
00:53:50,080 --> 00:53:53,038
We drove through
small villages and tiny hamlets.

778
00:53:53,160 --> 00:53:58,029
We had no great plan, but when we
stopped at an inn, fate provided one.

779
00:54:08,320 --> 00:54:12,598
Pardon me. Could you tell me
who those people are behind that screen?

780
00:54:12,720 --> 00:54:16,076
That's Don Francisco of Spain
and his sister.

781
00:54:16,200 --> 00:54:18,839
They're en route to meet Napoleon.

782
00:54:29,240 --> 00:54:32,994
- Don Francisco, I presume.
- Do you know me, señor?

783
00:54:33,120 --> 00:54:35,953
Oh, let's just say
your name is legend in these parts.

784
00:54:36,640 --> 00:54:39,074
- It is?
- Well, perhaps not legend,

785
00:54:39,200 --> 00:54:41,839
but it never fails to get a big laugh.

786
00:54:41,960 --> 00:54:46,795
And you must be the Don's sister,
the noted Spanish countess and mieskeit.

787
00:54:46,920 --> 00:54:48,831
Who are you?

788
00:54:48,960 --> 00:54:52,430
Just a humble servant
who wishes to buy His Excellency a drink.

789
00:54:52,560 --> 00:54:54,391
I would be honoured.

790
00:54:54,760 --> 00:54:59,197
Waiter, a bottle of your best red wine,
please, and two straws.

791
00:54:59,320 --> 00:55:01,436
Two straws.

792
00:55:01,560 --> 00:55:04,233
Word has it
the Don is en route to visit Napoleon.

793
00:55:05,680 --> 00:55:07,910
Word travels fast.

794
00:55:08,480 --> 00:55:11,358
Not as fast as good news.

795
00:55:11,880 --> 00:55:14,633
No news is good news.

796
00:55:14,920 --> 00:55:18,310
Here today, gone tomorrow.

797
00:55:19,120 --> 00:55:22,829
You can lead a horse to water,
but you can't make him drink.

798
00:55:22,960 --> 00:55:25,394
- Your turn.
- We would invite you to join us,

799
00:55:25,520 --> 00:55:29,798
but the difference in social rank and
wealth, it makes it silly.

800
00:55:30,200 --> 00:55:33,351
Oh, yes, I threw this on.
It's a knockdown.

801
00:55:34,440 --> 00:55:36,670
You guys know Napoleon, or what?

802
00:55:37,360 --> 00:55:39,555
Hardly.

803
00:55:41,560 --> 00:55:43,357
A joke, Your Nothingness?

804
00:55:43,480 --> 00:55:46,995
We're friends with his brother,
who arranges the affairs of Spain,

805
00:55:47,120 --> 00:55:50,590
but this is our first meeting
with the great emperor.

806
00:55:53,280 --> 00:55:54,952
It's all I wanted to know.

807
00:55:57,800 --> 00:56:00,633
- Don Francisco?
- Pardon me?

808
00:56:00,760 --> 00:56:03,513
I'm having trouble adjusting my belt.

809
00:56:04,120 --> 00:56:07,237
You think you could come over here
and hold my bosom for awhile?

810
00:56:08,840 --> 00:56:10,956
Of course, señorita.

811
00:56:51,840 --> 00:56:55,037
No, no, no, it's not what I had in mind.

812
00:56:55,640 --> 00:56:59,155
It should have more cream
between the crust and no raisins.

813
00:56:59,280 --> 00:57:02,397
- But at our last meeting you said raisins.
- No!

814
00:57:03,120 --> 00:57:07,796
If this pastry is to bear my name,
it must be richer! More cream.

815
00:57:07,920 --> 00:57:10,354
- Yes, but is there time?
- Very little.

816
00:57:10,480 --> 00:57:13,358
My spies tell me
that my illustrious British enemy

817
00:57:13,480 --> 00:57:18,349
is working on a new meat recipe
which he plans to call Beef Wellington.

818
00:57:18,480 --> 00:57:20,789
It will never get off the ground.

819
00:57:20,920 --> 00:57:24,754
We must develop the Napoleon
before he develops Beef Wellington.

820
00:57:26,320 --> 00:57:29,312
The future of Europe
hangs in the balance.

821
00:57:29,440 --> 00:57:31,396
Yes, Your Highness.

822
00:57:32,240 --> 00:57:34,196
We must see you, Your Highness.

823
00:57:35,360 --> 00:57:38,033
We believe there is a plot
to take your life.

824
00:57:38,160 --> 00:57:39,275
Vraiment?

825
00:57:39,400 --> 00:57:44,838
So we've made up an obscure private
from the ranks to look like you. Look.

826
00:57:44,960 --> 00:57:46,951
How do you do, Your Highness?

827
00:57:47,800 --> 00:57:51,588
- He looks like me?
- You're seeing him without his rug.

828
00:57:58,280 --> 00:58:02,068
- Come.
- Just let me get this on, Your Highness.

829
00:58:03,000 --> 00:58:06,515
And now I take your place.

830
00:58:07,200 --> 00:58:11,478
I will teach you to walk like me.
I have a great walk.

831
00:58:13,360 --> 00:58:17,751
With the emperor out of the way,
all that remains is to kill Don Francisco.

832
00:58:18,600 --> 00:58:23,151
That will destroy His Highness'
stupid dreams of a treaty with Spain.

833
00:58:24,320 --> 00:58:27,153
Then I'll sail to Austria,

834
00:58:27,800 --> 00:58:33,397
and form an alliance with the crown.
Not the king, just the crown.

835
00:58:34,440 --> 00:58:36,271
They call me mad,

836
00:58:36,400 --> 00:58:39,631
but one day,
when the history of France is written,

837
00:58:39,760 --> 00:58:41,910
they will mark my name well.

838
00:58:43,000 --> 00:58:44,956
Sidney Applebaum.

839
00:58:58,000 --> 00:58:59,956
We're here to see the emperor.

840
00:59:00,640 --> 00:59:02,676
Who is calling?

841
00:59:07,760 --> 00:59:10,513
- Who? Oh, that's droll!
- Droll, yes.

842
00:59:10,640 --> 00:59:14,553
He's not familiar with the list of
the hundred most important Spanishers.

843
00:59:14,680 --> 00:59:17,319
Yes.
It is only Don Francisco and his sister.

844
00:59:17,440 --> 00:59:19,396
Yes, the Donessa.

845
00:59:19,520 --> 00:59:21,476
We have an appointment with Napoleon.

846
00:59:21,600 --> 00:59:24,512
Napoleon Bonaparte.
The noted international tyrant.

847
00:59:24,640 --> 00:59:27,996
- You are Don Francisco and his sister?
- Oh, for sure.

848
00:59:28,120 --> 00:59:31,430
- We have had a long... a hot journey.
- A hot journey.

849
00:59:31,560 --> 00:59:33,949
- Our throats are parched.
- They're parched.

850
00:59:34,080 --> 00:59:36,548
- We seek succour. Succour.
- Succour!

851
00:59:36,680 --> 00:59:39,717
Yes. Is Succour here by any chance?

852
00:59:39,840 --> 00:59:42,912
I never knew your name, madam.

853
00:59:43,040 --> 00:59:46,350
The boys usually just call me Juanita.

854
00:59:51,640 --> 00:59:54,393
The emperor appreciates
magnificent women.

855
00:59:54,520 --> 00:59:57,353
- He'll be much taken with you.
- Oh, good! I wore my flats.

856
00:59:57,480 --> 01:00:00,870
We are, of course, all most anxious
to hear your proposal for a treaty.

857
01:00:01,000 --> 01:00:05,551
Good. I've given it a lot of thought
and I've come up with all the little details.

858
01:00:05,680 --> 01:00:08,717
If I can just think of the main points,
we got something!

859
01:00:08,840 --> 01:00:11,513
Let's leave business,
you've had a wearing journey.

860
01:00:11,640 --> 01:00:15,997
- We should say hello to the emperor.
- Shorts gets touchy if we bypass him.

861
01:00:16,120 --> 01:00:21,752
Later. First, you'll be wined and dined
in a manner befitting Spanish nobility.

862
01:00:21,880 --> 01:00:25,316
Oh, wonderful! But go easy on
the champagne. The Donessa has gout.

863
01:00:25,440 --> 01:00:28,477
Well, if you'll proceed,
your needs will be attended to.

864
01:00:28,600 --> 01:00:30,556
Thank you.

865
01:00:31,360 --> 01:00:35,433
While you're here with your sister,
should you desire a French love dream

866
01:00:35,560 --> 01:00:38,074
to be sent to your room,
it will be arranged.

867
01:00:38,200 --> 01:00:41,954
Good. Maybe I'll have two
to keep the symmetry perfect.

868
01:00:42,080 --> 01:00:46,631
- I prefer two myself.
- I prefer three, but it's hard to get one.

869
01:00:56,480 --> 01:00:59,153
Is this room big enough,
or would you prefer a suite?

870
01:00:59,280 --> 01:01:02,590
- Boris, I'm scared.
- You? I'm growing a beak and feathers.

871
01:01:02,720 --> 01:01:05,280
- What are we gonna do?
- I say we get outta here now.

872
01:01:05,400 --> 01:01:08,551
I'm not leaving here
until we shoot Napoleon. Here.

873
01:01:08,680 --> 01:01:10,716
Oh, I see. Thanks. I'm the hit man.

874
01:01:10,840 --> 01:01:13,832
Remember, you can't take any chances.

875
01:01:13,960 --> 01:01:19,239
Now, make sure the barrel of the gun
is pressed against his head or his chest.

876
01:01:19,360 --> 01:01:22,830
And don't pull the trigger, Boris.
Squeeze it.

877
01:01:23,640 --> 01:01:26,438
Where did you go to finishing school?
On a pirate ship?

878
01:01:26,560 --> 01:01:28,869
Let's just make sure
our plans are straight.

879
01:01:29,000 --> 01:01:32,356
OK. You flirt with him,
bring him back here after dinner,

880
01:01:32,480 --> 01:01:35,438
lull him into a state of satisfaction
and I'll shoot him.

881
01:01:35,560 --> 01:01:38,836
"I'll shoot him."
Can you believe I'm talking like this?

882
01:01:41,480 --> 01:01:44,677
Yes. Spain is quite warm this time of year.

883
01:01:44,800 --> 01:01:46,870
Barcelona is warmer than Madrid,

884
01:01:47,000 --> 01:01:51,596
but, then, the people are so different,
the Barcelonians and the Madridniks.

885
01:01:52,120 --> 01:01:55,635
Are all the ladies in Spain
as beautiful as you are, madam?

886
01:01:55,760 --> 01:01:58,320
Well, not all. You gotta have some beasts.

887
01:01:59,360 --> 01:02:00,509
Oh, General.

888
01:02:00,640 --> 01:02:02,995
Do excuse me, madam.

889
01:02:03,640 --> 01:02:05,995
Take it easy.
You're making a fool of yourself.

890
01:02:06,120 --> 01:02:09,590
- Hey, this is good champagne.
- Are you gonna drink another case?

891
01:02:09,720 --> 01:02:11,676
I'll be fine, all I need is a few solids.

892
01:02:11,800 --> 01:02:13,870
A few solids? You should drink a blotter.

893
01:02:14,000 --> 01:02:17,436
Oh, I believe I had the pleasure
of meeting your sister once.

894
01:02:17,560 --> 01:02:20,996
- My sister? Which one?
- I thought you only had one.

895
01:02:21,120 --> 01:02:22,917
One? Oh, no, no.

896
01:02:23,040 --> 01:02:25,838
Actually, well, I have a half-sister.

897
01:02:25,960 --> 01:02:29,509
Well, no, not exactly half. It's two-fifths.

898
01:02:29,640 --> 01:02:31,198
Ladies and gentlemen,

899
01:02:31,320 --> 01:02:34,835
His lmperial Highness,
the Emperor Napoleon.

900
01:02:44,880 --> 01:02:48,509
- So you are Don Francisco?
- Yes. I have regards from your brother.

901
01:02:48,640 --> 01:02:51,916
Says you went away, you don't write.
He never hears from you.

902
01:02:52,040 --> 01:02:54,110
You took his razor,
you never returned it.

903
01:02:54,240 --> 01:02:56,754
- This is an honour for me.
- It's a greater honour for me.

904
01:02:56,880 --> 01:02:59,599
- No, a greater honour for me.
- No, a greater honour for me.

905
01:02:59,720 --> 01:03:03,190
- No, a greater honour for me.
- Well, perhaps it is a greater for you.

906
01:03:03,320 --> 01:03:06,915
- You must be Don Francisco's sister.
- You must be Don Francisco's sister.

907
01:03:07,040 --> 01:03:10,999
- No, you must be Don Francisco's sister.
- No, you must be Don Francisco's sister.

908
01:03:11,120 --> 01:03:14,908
- No, it's a greater honour for me.
- Our guests have a sense of humour.

909
01:03:15,040 --> 01:03:17,508
- She's a great kidder.
- No, you're a great kidder.

910
01:03:17,640 --> 01:03:19,471
No, you're Don Francisco's sister.

911
01:03:19,600 --> 01:03:21,875
- Shall we dine?
- Oh, can we eat first?

912
01:03:31,520 --> 01:03:35,718
Your sister and His Highness
seem to be getting along quite well.

913
01:03:35,840 --> 01:03:37,876
Do you find me attractive as a man?

914
01:03:38,000 --> 01:03:40,036
Yes. I think that's your best bet.

915
01:03:40,640 --> 01:03:44,155
How much of your feelings for me
are because I rule half of Europe?

916
01:03:44,280 --> 01:03:46,350
Oh, I'd say half my feelings. It evens out.

917
01:03:46,480 --> 01:03:49,313
Will you be more difficult
to conquer than Russia?

918
01:03:49,440 --> 01:03:51,158
Well, I weigh less.

919
01:03:51,280 --> 01:03:54,590
- I'll go to your room after dinner.
- Good. I'll go to yours.

920
01:04:02,080 --> 01:04:04,036
Come in.

921
01:04:05,600 --> 01:04:09,309
Sonja, I've been thinking
about this. It's murder.

922
01:04:09,440 --> 01:04:12,238
If everybody did this,
it'd be a world full of murderers.

923
01:04:12,360 --> 01:04:14,828
- What would that do to property values?
- I know.

924
01:04:14,960 --> 01:04:17,679
If everybody went to
the same restaurant one evening

925
01:04:17,800 --> 01:04:20,394
to eat blintzes, there'd be chaos.
But they don't.

926
01:04:20,520 --> 01:04:22,988
I tell her murder. She tells me blintzes.

927
01:04:23,120 --> 01:04:25,554
Hey, you said yourself
there is no right or wrong.

928
01:04:25,680 --> 01:04:27,910
- It's what you choose.
- That's right,

929
01:04:28,040 --> 01:04:29,951
and I choose danger.

930
01:04:30,080 --> 01:04:33,277
- Oh, really?
